ISLAMABAD, Jan 19 (APP): Minister of State for Information and Broadcasting Farrukh Habib on Wednesday said Prime Minister Imran Khan was the only leader, who had the courage to say “Absolutely Not” to those who wanted to exercise more oppression on Pakistanis.
The minister said in a tweet that he was proud of his leader, and he had voted and supported him. He would again vote for Imran Khan in the 2023 general election.
